edu.gatech.mbse.plugins.papyrus.sysml2milp.tests

Class TestBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.gatech.mbse.plugins.papyrus.sysml2milp.tests.TestBase
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExpertKnowledgeLimitingInstancesTest, ExpertKnowledgeTest, ParallelProcessTest, ResourceSetSizeConstraintTest, SequentialProcessTest, ThroughputConstraintTest, ThroughputOptimizationTest

    public class TestBase
extends java.lang.Object
    Base class for tests of SysML2MILP transformation. This is a collection of procedures for loading UML models and registering profiles outside of Papyrus and in a standalone Java application.
    Version:
    0.1.0
    Author:
    Sebastian J. I. Herzig

        public void loadProject(org.eclipse.emf.common.util.URI model,
               java.util.Map<java.lang.String,org.eclipse.emf.common.util.URI> profilesToRegister)
        Loads a UML model and registers any specified profiles. Note that the SysML profile is loaded automatically.
        Parameters:
        model - An URI object pointing to the location of the UML model.
        profilesToRegister - A mapping from namespace URIs (as strings) to location of a profile definition (as URI object).

      • executeTransformation

        protected java.lang.String executeTransformation(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Activity process,
                                     int numSolutionsToGenerate)
                                          throws java.lang.Exception
        Executes the transformation.

        Note that the solver can be set via JVM options: just define the property milp.solver when launching the tests (e.g., via maven command line or jenkins).

        Parameters:
        process - Top level activity.
        numSolutionsToGenerate - The number of solutions to generate.
        Returns:
        Generated MILP in YALMIP format.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • executeMatlabScript

      • compareActualToExpectedOutput

        protected void compareActualToExpectedOutput(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> expectedMappings)
        Compares the actual output to expected mappings. Note that, currently, only properties of the manufacturing cell (at the top level) are output into the temporary file (but this can be changed fairly easily in the transformation).
        Parameters:
        expectedMappings - A hash map object of expected mappings.
